**Abstract:**
Formal memo from Xavier O. Monasterio to ACPAS Ad Hoc Committee members regarding proposed ordinances for Catholic colleges and universities by American bishops. Expresses sympathy for bishops' concerns about theological teaching but recommends prudential delay in implementing ordinances beyond pontifical universities. Argues ordinances risk polarization and threatens survival of Catholic universities. Cites reluctance of university presidents and notes movement to reaffirm Catholic identity in American Catholic universities. References Pope John Paul II's *Ex Corde Ecclesiae*.

**AI Recommendation:** Keep in undated/notes OR move to correspondence folder - institutional correspondence

